250 g Mild Italian Sausage, uncased
1 unit(s) Cannellini Beans
113 g Mirepoix
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
28 g Arugula and Spinach Mix
113 mL Cream
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
½ cup Sun-Dried Tomato Pesto
5 g Italian Herb Spice Blend
10 g Cream Sauce Spice Blend
28 g Crispy Shallots
1.33 tbsp Oil*
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.06 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch pieces.

Heat a large pot over medium-high.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, sausage, mirepoix, peppers and Italian Herb Spice Blend. Season with salt and pepper. Cook for 4-6 min, breaking up sausage into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.**

Sprinkle Cream Sauce Spice Blend over top. Stir to coat.
Add beans and their liquid, cream, pesto and 3/4 cup (1 1/2 cups) water.
Bring to a boil over high, then reduce heat to medium. Cook for 3-5 min, stirring often, until lightly thickened. (TIP: If you prefer a brothier stew, add more water, 1/4 cup at a time.)

When stew is almost done, to a large bowl, add Parmesan, arugula and spinach mix and 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil. Season with pepper. Toss to coat. (TIP: For extra brightness, add a squeeze of lemon juice!)

Divide stew beween bowls.
Top with Parmesan-dressed greens.
Sprinkle crispy shallots over top.